    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Average streamwise velocity as a function of the wall normal distance for (a) $\mathrm{St}^&amp;#43; = 6$ and (b) $\mathrm{St}^&amp;#43; = 30$ at various mass loadings. The solid black line represents the particle-free channel. Darker symbols correspond to larger mass loadings which vary from 0.2-1.0.&#34; srcset=&#34;
